				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I always thought of clipping as capping (stopping at max value) because that's how the term is <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Audio_clipping" class="postlink">usually used in audio</a>.  But it does make logical sense to use it the other way, as well.  Due to the confusion I've been trying to refrain from using that term in my code and things.  I find myself using 'cap' instead.
<br />
<br />I tend to use 'wrap' for the opposite... since that term leaves little/no room for confusion.
<br />
<br />But yeah... whatever.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

