						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">That's great, as it's possible to redefine the reset code yourself without affecting the existing one, then disable ROM instantly without risking to have the CPU crashing if the programm is reset at that time.</div>
<br />Nope, the IPL ROM is switched back in when the SNES is reset. The ROM is good for getting initial code in, and little else, since its functionality can be duplicated by the uploaded code, and it occupies the area where the table for the optimized TCALL instruction is.</div>

